storyInfo: Mousse makes plans to welcome her mother to Rhodes Island, but things go awry right off the bat.

attributes.content: Meow—
attributes.name: Spotted

attributes.content: (Sorry, kitties, I can't play with you today.)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Here's where I live, mummy.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: By yourself, sweetheart?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: No, I have a roommate to keep me company.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Is that right...? I had no idea. I would've brought a gift for her.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Don't worry about it.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: She's out on a mission right now and won't be back for a while. She says you can have her bed for these few days, if you want.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Well... I booked a hotel in a nearby city.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Right... I understand. A hotel would be more comfortable, after all.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: The room may be nice, but it would be too empty without my precious daughter. I'm not sure I'd be able to sleep.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: So you'll stay here?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (Touches Mousse's nose) Yes, sweetheart.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I knew you were coming, so I spent an entire day cleaning up! Everything's sparkling!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Have you forgotten? You didn't even need to make your own bed at home.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Rhodes Island isn't like home. I have to do a lot on my own. It took some time to get used to, but I've learned a lot.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: At first, I didn't know how to put the comforter into its cover.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I kept struggling with it, but I just couldn't get it done.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Guess what happened when I finally managed to get it zipped up?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I almost zipped myself in with it! Hah!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (Embarrassed smile) That's really something... haha.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Close your eyes, mummy!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Just close them for a little bit.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Hm... alright.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I guarantee you'll be shocked when you see my room.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I certainly am shocked, sweetheart.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Oh no, mummy... it wasn't like that this morning...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: 'Kitties' run rampant around the messy room.
The curtains have been reduced to barely-recognizable ribbons.
Less fortunate are the vases formerly on the table, with the broken shards on the ground the only sign that they were ever there in the first place.
A 'Kitty' stands on the table, preparing to leap over to the nearby wardrobe.
Mousse looks up to the wardrobe, a vase teeters by the edge, looking like it could fall at any second.
(Jumps on top of the wardrobe)
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: Meow!
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: No! Not the vases!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Meow?
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: Bad kitty!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: How could you do this! You're all bad kitties!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's ok, sweetheart. They're mischievous creatures.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Sorry, mummy. This isn't what I had meant to show you. I really did clean up.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I know, sweetheart. Let's find a place to sit down and figure out how to put everything back in its proper place.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Let's see... is there anywhere we can sit?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Watch out! There's yarn on the floor!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Watch out for—Aiee!
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Are you alright?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I'm fine... it's just...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I'll call Medical!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: No, I'm not hurt. I just stepped on my dress when I tripped, and I think...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I think I put a hole in it.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: That was a long day... I'm sore all over.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Didn't you have the day off?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I was preparing for mummy's visit. I've been on edge for days.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Shouldn't you be happy to have family visiting? Why so nervous?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I've always been worried about disappointing mummy. My siblings are all outstanding, while I'm totally unremarkable.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I've no achievements to speak of, and I caught an illness that can't be spoken of...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Don't be so down on yourself. Wasn't the Doctor just raving about your incredible progress a few days ago?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: It's... It's not enough. You don't know how incredible my siblings are.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Byron is already a lieutenant colonel, and Emily is consulting for several different banks straight out of school.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Violet is an authority on Originium Arts research. And my youngest brother, Carl...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Violet? That Violet?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Yes, that Violet. She's my older sister.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Alright... I don't blame you for being nervous, then.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I got compared to them whenever I attended a gathering.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mummy always defended me, but she's a proud woman, and she must be ashamed to have a daughter like me.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: That's what I hate about high society. The gossip never stops.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: That's why I wanted to show her how much I've grown.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Mrs. Selis. My name is Bibeak, and I'm a friend of Mousse's.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Thank you for mending my skirt, Miss Bibeak.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I really appreciate it.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Er, I'm very glad I could help. Yes. Indeed.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: (Mousse's mother doesn't seem like the chatty type... wherever has Mousse gone? How long will we have to sit here staring at each other?)
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: (But what can we even talk about? Argh, I'll just pick a random topic...)
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: (Takes a deep breath) Mrs. Selis, I...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Mummy, I made your favorite almond cake.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (Finally!)
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: And I made a custard tart for you, Bibeak. It's your favorite, isn't it?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Thank you, Mousse! I've mended Mrs. Selis's skirt. Her blouse is fine.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Miss Bibeak did a splendid job. It's like the hole was never there.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: G-Great! Let me know whenever you'd care for a pastry. I, I'd love to make you anything.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: No need to go that far. You should sit down too. I'm sure Mrs. Selis can't wait to taste the cake.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Come, sweetheart, I haven't had your cake in ages.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: R-Right.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: How is it?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's delicious.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Yes. Just the perfect level of sweetness and moistness. It's so... agh!
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What's the matter?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I think I got something strange in my mouth.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What are these? Hairs?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Oh no, it's kitty hair! Don't eat any more. I'll get you another piece.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Sorry, they must have gotten in when I forgot to lock the kitchen door.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's alright, sweetheart. I don't mind at all.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: But mummy...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's alright, really.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (But your eyes are turning red...)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mousse...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Ahem. I believe you're a designer, Miss Bibeak? Are you familiar with the latest trends?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: My usual tailor is rather conservative, and I would like to get some dresses that are more in fashion.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What do young people like you enjoy in dresses?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Huh? Oh... knit details have been popular the past couple years.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Knit details... I remember when they were all the rage ten years ago. Or was it fifteen?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: You know what they say about fashion. It all comes back around.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: (Twiddles fingers in silence)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Here's your food, Mousse. I hope you ladies enjoy it.
attributes.name: Hung

attributes.content: (Looks at her cup of tea)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Sweetheart?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Huh? Oh... wait, I didn't order this many dishes, did I?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's on the house. Always an occasion when an operator gets a family visit.
attributes.name: Hung

attributes.content: They need me in the kitchen. Eat up.
attributes.name: Hung

attributes.content: Thank you, Hung.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Is the chef your friend too?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Hung knows how to make a lot of Yanese desserts. I pick his brain from time to time.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's a nice change of pace. You used to be alone all the time, with only your kitties to keep you company.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: And we're always so busy that we couldn't give you the care and attention you needed...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: You and daddy did everything you could to protect me!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I made a lot of friends here, but I've always missed you and daddy. I was so excited when I heard you were coming.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: My pay isn't very high, but I've managed to save some money.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Sweetheart... this is...?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I bought a tea set from Croissant. I hope you don't mind that it's not as nice as the ones you have at home...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (hands over the chest) Oh... I would never denigrate a gift from you.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What a beautiful tray! It's so pretty that I'm hesitant to even use it. Maybe I should just put it on display for everyone to see.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: As you like. I wanted to show you what I can do, but I keep making mistakes...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Are you still bothered by that? I told you, it was nothing to be upset about.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: But I saw... wait, a kitty in the cafeteria?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Where's the kitty?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: B-Behind you.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mroaaaw—!
attributes.name: Spotted

attributes.content: Whoah! Not on the table, kitty!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Oh no, my cup!
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Bad kitty! You're all bad kitties!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: You're awful!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Why did you have to make a mess in front of mummy?!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I spent so much time cleaning up and saving money to buy her a present... bad kitties!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Don't cry, sweetheart...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Stands up)
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: What's the matter, Mousse? I heard you crying from the kitchen.
attributes.name: Hung

attributes.content: Just leave the pieces where they are, Mousse. I'll get a broom.
attributes.name: Mint

attributes.content: It's alright, Mousse. I've got plenty of tea sets. Come over and pick one you like.
attributes.name: Jessica

attributes.content: What's all this then? Who's making my little Mousse cry? Give me a name, my hat and I'll show 'em what for.
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: No... it's all my fault for not being good enough...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Don't say that about yourself!
attributes.name: Everyone

attributes.content: Phew—
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (What a relief.)
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Come closer. Let me wipe your hair dry.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: You cut your hair short. I remember you used to like it long.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: It was troublesome out in the field, and when baking, so I cut it.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It's fine. You look very pretty with short hair too.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Come, sweetheart, it's time for bed.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Mummy...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Are you sure you want to squeeze into my bed?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: You don't want me to?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: That's not it, I'm just worried you won't sleep well.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Violet said you hardly slept when you visited her, and you were staying in a five-star hotel.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Could you really sleep in a tiny bed with me?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Ah... it wasn't because of the bed that I had trouble sleeping.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Violet had an accident the day before, leaving a huge scar on her forehead. I was so worried that I couldn't sleep.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Luckily, it wasn't anything serious. She gave her lecture the following day as scheduled, and the crowd wouldn't stop clapping when she finished.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: You must have been proud.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Of course. Violet was always a bright girl. I hardly had to worry about her. Unlike Carl, who kept running around after breaking his elbow last month.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Did he get hurt in a match?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Yes, and he hid it until the final whistle. He didn't want to be taken out. Your father had words for him when he learned.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Did they win?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Of course... there isn't a better team in the age group.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: *yawn*...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Retreats into the sheets)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mummy...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Are you disappointed in me?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Violet and Carl have done so much to make you proud, but I haven't... I'm not talented. I don't have any special skills.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I didn't get good grades in school. All I did was make you worry after I got sick. You had to take time off work to be with me.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I'm sorry.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I could never make you proud.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (Turns) Mummy?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Sweetheart...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Reaches for the other side of the bed)
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Sweetheart? Where did she go? The sun isn't up yet... there's nobody in the bathroom either.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Meow...
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: Kitty...?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Do you know where my sweetheart is, little one?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Drops head and licks own butt)
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: Don't ignore me, kitty.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Keeps licking own butt)
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: I know you must feel neglected because Mousse has been busy preparing for my visit. That's why you tried to get her attention.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Sorry. On her behalf.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Meow...
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: (Strokes kitty's chin)
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Are you still upset?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Meow.
attributes.name: Striped

attributes.content: Will you take me to her?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: The kitty rubs itself against Mrs. Selis's feet, then goes over to the door and looks at her, as though telling her to follow.
It's already six? I have to get that bread baked before breakfast...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: How could I oversleep?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: It must be because I was relaxed around mummy... the dough's ready. Now for the filling.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: (Starts whipping cream)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Aw... why does my hand have to itch right now?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I want to scratch it.... no, I'd better not, I won't be able to stop.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Let me help you, sweetheart.
Mummy?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: W-What are you doing here? Did I wake you up?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Are you always up so early making breakfast for the others?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: It's the only thing I'm good at. And I like to do it.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I never got much chance to do this at home, but it makes me happy to something I'm good at here.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Oh, sweetheart...
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: How far along are you? I'll help you.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: It's alright, I can do it on my own.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Let's see. The dough's ready. I can help with the filling. You're using cream?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Er, yes. But mummy...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Shh, sweetheart. This is some mother and daughter time. It's been ages since we baked bread together.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Yes, mummy.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Please make the fillings then.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mother and daughter go back and forth from the kitchen table to the oven.
There is hardly any talking. A slight gesture, a blink of the eye, is all the communication they need.
Fowlbeast eggs are broken and their contents dropped into bowls. Cream is whipped until filled with air. Syrup is brushed on the dough. Hot air seeps out of the pre-heated oven.
The sounds in the kitchen make a symphony of their own.
We did it, mummy!
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Yes, sweetheart, we did.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Just in time for breakfast.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Yes, just in time for breakfast.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Maybe we can do a little more...?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Do what?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Sprinkles a layer of icing on the bread)
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Now it's perfect.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Agreed.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: (Gaze at each other)
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis & Mousse

attributes.content: I'm proud of you, sweetheart. Very proud.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Huh...?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I've never told you that, have I?
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Why? I know you're proud of Byron, of Emily, of Violet, and Carl. They're all outstanding.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: But I'm just Mousse... I'm not anything.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I've got two tails, I'm bad at maths, I don't know my grammar, I have Oripathy... and my hands get itchy when I have an Oripathy attack.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I don't care about any of that.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Then what do you care about?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mummy only cares that you're happy and doing what you love.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I fought with your father a lot over whether to send you here.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I didn't want you going to this place on your own. It wouldn't be as comfortable as home, and we couldn't be there for you if anything happened.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Before I visited, I was thinking I would bring you back if you didn't like it here, even if I had to pummel your father into it.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: But you're happy here... you're not alone anymore. You have lots of friends who care for you.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: But I couldn't welcome you the way Violet could.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: That's rubbish, sweetheart. I've had a delightful time!
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: But you had tears in your eyes when you found kitty fur in your cake yesterday...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: You've got it all wrong.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I was happy.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: You were?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: I haven't enjoyed a pastry of yours in so long. Not since you got sick.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I had an even more pleasant surprise when I walked into kitchen. You've started baking again, you're... you're still doing what you love here.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: I never knew...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Mousse, my little sweetheart.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Mousse, I have a lesson this morning, so I need two to go... oh, good morning, ma'am.
attributes.name: Anxious Young Operator

attributes.content: Er, good morning.
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Two to go, Zeiss? Here you are.
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: Thanks... hmm, I've never seen this kind of bread. What is it?
attributes.name: Anxious Young Operator

attributes.content: I just made it with the ingredients at hand. There isn't any...
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: 'Mother's Pride.'
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Mousse & Anxious Young Operator?

attributes.content: The name of the bread is 'Mother's Pride.'
attributes.name: Mrs. Selis
